sentences.english: With the eyes nine-tenths closed, focus at the tip of your nose.
sentences.chinese: 眼睛閉上十分之九，注意力集中在鼻尖。

sentences.english: The length of laser tube was reduced ten times.
sentences.chinese: 激光管的長度縮短了十分之九。

sentences.english: But it had a nine million dollar surplus in cranberries.
sentences.chinese: 但卻有九百萬美元的蔓越橘的剩餘。

sentences.english: Today is September ninth by lunar calendar. It's the Double Ninth Festival.
sentences.chinese: 今天是農曆九月初九，是重陽節。

sentences.english: Hiroshima took nine seconds; Changchun took five months.
sentences.chinese: 廣島用了九秒鐘，長春用了五個月。

sentences.english: Matsuzawa trained chimps to recognize the numbers one through nine.
sentences.chinese: Matsuzawa訓練過猩猩識別一到九的數字。

sentences.english: I've missed more than nine thousand shots in my career. I've lost almost three hundred games.
sentences.chinese: 我投失了九千多個球，輸了幾乎三百場球賽。

sentences.english: B: Pay cash for this one and then we'll see what we can do.
sentences.chinese: 立即付款的話可以有九八折，三十天內付款需付全額。

sentences.english: Almost nine hours later, the 47-year-old landed nearly 200 miles from home.
sentences.chinese: 大約九小時後，降落在離家約200公里的地方。

sentences.english: A gift may be subject to obligations.
sentences.chinese: 第一百九十條贈與可以附義務。

sentences.english: Houston last reeled off nine victories in a row on the road in 1993.
sentences.chinese: 火箭隊最近一次取得客場九連勝是在1993年。

sentences.english: Also, in the Mayan tradition the number Nine plays a predominating role.
sentences.chinese: 此外，在傳統的瑪雅數字九統領作用的發揮。

sentences.english: Over nine-tenths of China's inhabitants belong to the Han nationality.
sentences.chinese: 中國人口的十分之九以上是漢族。

sentences.english: Marion checked nine books out from the library.
sentences.chinese: 瑪莉安從圖書館借了九本書。

sentences.english: There is no restriction on the number of participants from each organisation.
sentences.chinese: 全程約九千米，參加者年齡不限。

sentences.english: Therefore, only when we attain Buddhahood, can we perfectly help all beings in the universe.
sentences.chinese: 因此，一定要成佛道，才能夠廣度九法界一切衆生。
